website_summaries.verdict: Great choice for owners of heavier vehicles, even commercial size. Strong brand name and great design/engineering. Extra length and a carrying case.
pros: Heavy 1 gauge copper-clad aluminum wire strong enough for trucks and SUVs
Can reach battery without front-to-front alignment
cons: Heavier gauge may be more than average drivers need
Side post batteries can be a challenge for clamps
Plastic clamp hinge prone to breakage

customer_reviews.title: Item not as pictured/described!!
customer_reviews.text: Nothing like the one pictured. I recieved clamps that have one side extended so it makes them very hard to secure a proper connection. The ones pictured would have been great.
customer_reviews.author: Kyle

customer_reviews.title: I have used them twice, both times on vehicles ...
customer_reviews.text: I have used them twice, both times on vehicles I have jumped before with a decent set of cables (6 gauge). there was a noticeable difference. both cars had completely dead batteries and both started immediately. Previously I had to let them charge up a minute or two before they would start. I had to sew a new front on the bag, The plastic panel split out the first time I used it.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Money well spent
customer_reviews.text: These booster cables have strong alligator clamps, for # 1 gauge they are remarkably pliable and coil back nicely even in below freezing temps. What struck me about these cables are how well they transfer current ! My truck battery was weak . I hooked up my vw with engine at idle and there was a drop in RPMs. Previous times I would need to rev my engine to transfer current. These cables transfer current with little resistance. Its the most money I've ever spent on booster cables but I feel its money well spent . very happy with my purchase
customer_reviews.author: Rick M

customer_reviews.title: Energizer Pincer Clamps Not Centered - See Photo
customer_reviews.text: The pincer clamps are not centered (see attached photo). The pincers are all off-center to the same side which leads me to believe it is a manufacturing issue. They are made in China, so that may explain it. Energizer (i.e., Bright Manufacturing) should improve it’s Quality Control!!!
customer_reviews.author: Jeff

customer_reviews.title: The case is a little too lightweight and small to easily store the cables after use
customer_reviews.text: These are heavy and long - but they work extremely well. The clamps are probably the sturdiest I've ever used for jumper cables and solved my problem with awkward shaped areas that some other clamps tended to slip off from. They were consistently starting batteries that would not start with cheap cables, which is kindof the main goal of jumper cables in the first place. The case is a little too lightweight and small to easily store the cables after use, but if you can get them in there it will be pretty compact considering how much wire there is.
customer_reviews.author: G. Graham

customer_reviews.title: Nice Heavy Duty Cables
customer_reviews.text: We needed a longer set of jumper cables and I found these while searching on Amazon. They are very well made and came in a nice carry pouch. They are very long and look like they should last a long time. So far we have not had to put them to use so I can tell you is about the way they look and how they came packaged.
customer_reviews.author: MJ

customer_reviews.title: Poor Quality
customer_reviews.text: Had high hopes, based on other reviews, but a clamp broke during the first use.
customer_reviews.author: St. Louis

customer_reviews.title: Received a Different Item Than Pictured
customer_reviews.text: Like many others who ordered this product, I received a different item than is pictured. The ones I received had an extension on the front that made it impossible to clamp onto the battery terminals. Once I got them clamped on (barely) it didn't work at all. Borrowed other more traditional jumper cables and the car started right up. So not only are they frustrating to use, but also ineffective.
customer_reviews.author: Jessica

customer_reviews.title: Doesn't work on all cars
customer_reviews.text: This works well, but you can't actually clamp top-down like you can with other cables, meaning it won't work on cars with a battery in the trunk and have a jump point on the front, like my 2005 Volvo V70. It's really hard to get the trunk open on this car when the battery is dead, but I managed to get it open by jamming a metal rod somewhere, and once I had access to the battery it was a breeze. While the value is good, I'll be returning these for a cable that can clamp top-down.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Worked Well
customer_reviews.text: Purchased after some random person asked if I had jumpers - Well I didn't, so I thought I wouldn't want to be in that predicament if I needed a jump. I have only used it once to help someone out, it worked as could be expected. Fitting back into the bag is a bit hard or maybe it's just I've never been too good at refolding these kinds of things. I do like the fact it has a bag to keep it together. Price is good for what it is and the clamps are strong. I hope to get many years of service out of these.
customer_reviews.author: Richard G

customer_reviews.title: Buy the lowest gauge you can
customer_reviews.text: I don’t believe they are 4g. They are not heavy They would not start a truck with out letting battery charge for 7min ( mind that 20+ feet is quite a long distance for these cables). I did try my old 4g 10foot copper cables and they did start the truck.( I did this just before I let the new cables charge the battery just to see) . Good clips, very flexible cables. I’d buy the lowest gauge next. That
customer_reviews.author: Yvonne J.

customer_reviews.title: Amazing jumper cables
customer_reviews.text: Great jumper cables. I’ve never owned such heavy duty cables and what a difference. I could t jump a dead battery with some cheap thin cables I had and bought these and jumped the dead battery literally in seconds. Also the length is excellent don’t under estimate this convenience. I jumped from the front of one SUV up over another SUV with no problem. The bag zipper as mentioned by others breaks immediately but I didn’t buy this for the bag so don’t care.
customer_reviews.author: J Bennett

customer_reviews.title: impressively thick cable. And the length is needed sometimes, don't get a shorter one.
customer_reviews.text: I did not expect the thickness, it was excellent and a good value. Most of all, after having ended up an annoying foot or two "too darn short" after ordering and trying shorter jumper cables---12 and 15 footers never quite get there sometimes except in a perfect world----these are the better length. Think about how long a couple SUV's would be, now picture them not being able to get up right next to each other for some reason, and it happens. Splurge for this slightly longer length and you will never be sorry. Comes in a nice durable hard plastic case.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Cables look great in the packaging
customer_reviews.text: Cables looked great in the packaging. When I tried to use them, months later, I almost bought a new battery. The funky teeth on the cable clamps were not transferring the power. After about 15 minutes, I broke out my handy multimeter and figured this out. I would not recommend these cables.
customer_reviews.author: Randy

customer_reviews.title: Looks high quality
customer_reviews.text: Hadnt had the chance to use these yet, but out of the box they seem of good quality. Everything is as advertised. I opted to buy the higher quality jumpers because I was in a situation where all I had was a battery booster and a really dead battery. The booster didn't have the amps needed to get me started, but a good set of jumpers did. I'd like to avoid another situation like that if at all possible so I bought the 1 gauge jumpers. If its got the power to start a transfer truck, it can start my car!
customer_reviews.author: Kyle

customer_reviews.title: I bought based on review rating and carrying/storage case
customer_reviews.text: Immediately upon opening the box for this product I noticed the carry bag it comes in was already split down the center of the. The clear plastic liner of the bag had a split right down the middle as if it’s a little old and some dry rot. Other than that it’s fine. I sort of purchased this for the carry bag for organization so that is why my review is 4/5 stars
customer_reviews.author: Joshua

customer_reviews.title: don't do what I did...
customer_reviews.text: I am disappointed because the picture fooled me into thinking the entire clamp was covered with a plastic/vinyl. Only the very tips in the clamping area is covered this way. The picture on the packaging almost looks like they took some of the gloss off of the painted surface to make it look more plastic.
customer_reviews.author: Gord - San Clemente

customer_reviews.title: Twice the Cable, Half the Price
customer_reviews.text: This is a quality set of jumper cables. Well made and flexible. My old set felt like it was melting just trying to jump start the mower (cheap roadside kit), but not these. These Energizer cables have strong clamps that grab and hold on. I was always wiggling my old cables to get them to make a good connection. These may be bigger than needed, but if your cables are to small it will ruin them. I think that's what happened to my old ones. For $30 these are worth every cent , so glad I didn't buy the $20 set, basically the same ones I had.
customer_reviews.author: Hill Billy

customer_reviews.title: High quality product. Hard to use on side mounted battery
customer_reviews.text: Good quality product. Cables were thick and cranked my truck pretty quickly. Decent length (I have the 20 ft version). Not sure if I can jump from behind my truck but will update if I can. My only complaint is that the way the teeth where you connect to the battery is aligned makes it a bit difficult for a side mounted battery connect. Took a little while to get it to stay on the battery. U cannot use the sides of the clamp you have to use the end. On a top mounted battery it was quick and easy to connect.
customer_reviews.author: Matthew Enriquez

customer_reviews.title: Seem Ok So Far
customer_reviews.text: I don't normally review items this early, but Energizer insisted to get the extra warranty so here goes. I have not used them yet other than to take out of the package and store in the vehicle. In the bag, the cables would not fit in the storage bay so I had to take out of bag and store elsewhere. Tips seem to be sturdy with copper ends. Overall they seem to be proper cables of reasonable length an likely durability for the price. Hopefully when the time comes to use them they will work.
customer_reviews.author: Look585

customer_reviews.title: Coils Good, Bag Bad
customer_reviews.text: The cables are great. Just what you’d expect. The bag they came in, however, is terrible. First, it’s too small. Everyone knows that once you take something out of its original packaging, it’s hard to get it back in. Well, good luck coiling these cables small and tight enough to get them back in the bag. Second, the bag ripped! As I was trying to squeeze the cables back in, the seam busted. It’s not worth sending them back. I can find another bag to store them in. But still—disappointing!
customer_reviews.author: l2shadesofpurple

customer_reviews.title: Super Duty Lifetime Cable
customer_reviews.text: I bought a second set after buying my first one. These are heavy and long. Did I say heavy? I expect them to be the last jumper cables I ever buy. The clamps are well insulated. The gripping is a little odd with all the clamp insulation around it but should be fine. Carrying case is marginal. I haven't tried yet to remove the cables and get them back into the case. My only concern with these is getting into tight spaces or camping to small posts or side terminals. Time will tell. I'll update this review if things change. This review is fo the 4 gauge 20ft cables
customer_reviews.author: ArcticMinibike

customer_reviews.title: Inexpensive, works, anchors to the battery terminals well
customer_reviews.text: Not much to say about these. They seem reasonably well made, are very inexpensive, and work - I've used them a couple times already (unfortunately). Only downside is it's pretty hard to package them back into the included zippered bag after you've unrolled the cables. The bag could've been a tiny bit bigger.
customer_reviews.author: Potentially You

customer_reviews.title: JUMP WHAT?!?
customer_reviews.text: I bought these as a gift for my Moms neighbor, he helped her recently and she told me about the difficult time he had because of his old cables and how difficult it was to get them to clamp on. Naturally, I came to Amazon and found this Energizer set, they’re exactly what he needs...the end of the clamp will fit his needs perfectly! The cables are heavy duty, extra long and they’re a gift for him being so nice to my Mom. It’s a win win win!! : )
customer_reviews.author: R

customer_reviews.title: Do not buy these if you have a side post battery.
customer_reviews.text: I bought this to jump a battery. THEY WILL NOT WORK FOR SIDE POST BATTERIES AS THEY COME. I need to bed then to get them to seat on a side post. I called the company and the guys response was well we all 10's of thousands of these so they must be good. They suck to actually jump a side post battery. DO NOT BUY THESE IF YOU ACTUALLY WANT TO USE THEM.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: MY HUSBAND IS PLEASED
customer_reviews.text: My husband told me to buy a pair of jumper cables. I came home with a nice emergency kit that had a pair of jumper cables in it and thought I had done well. Well, I didn't. I was told the jumper cable wires were too small. I got online and looked up recommended jumper cables and found the pair of ENB216. For the money they seemed to be the best buy. I ordered them; they came in, and my husband seemed pleased. While thankfully he has not needed to use them yet, he feels like if he needs to be jumped off or needs to jump off someone else, he has what would be needed.
customer_reviews.author: A Grandmother

customer_reviews.title: Pretty sure you'd melt the insulation if you tried running ...
customer_reviews.text: clamps are very strong, look well made. 800 amps may be an exaggeration. Pretty sure you'd melt the insulation if you tried running 800 amps through a 1 gauge wire, especially copper over aluminum. They are more than capable of jump starting any car or interrogating a captured spy
customer_reviews.author: David Gore

customer_reviews.title: These cables saved my life
customer_reviews.text: I only had them for 3 days now and I NEVER expected to use them this soon My car wasn’t starting And yet I only have my temps driving with my dad I asked a lady if she’s able to help us jump out car since i has the cables she was ina. Rush and unfortunately she wasn’t able to help right away but she drove to a police officer near by to assist us to jump out car Both my Dad and the officer were surprised of how good these cables were and the length were amazing I am so thankful I bought these and the shipping case right on time thankfully
customer_reviews.author: Leah hoctor

customer_reviews.title: I'm prepared now!
customer_reviews.text: I only gave this product 4 stars because I have not yet used them. I expect them to work well. Before Christmas I came out of the grocery store to find my battery DEAD. Unloaded my trunk to find that my longtime cables were missing. I have no idea what happened. I decided that I needed to be more prepared. I do like the case that the cables are in and the 20 feet length will be helpful, I am sure.
customer_reviews.author: Dixie Deb

customer_reviews.title: Excellent set of jumper cables...
customer_reviews.text: So my wife and I were out driving one day this spring and stopped to eat a perch sandwich. Since the restaurant was closed inside (due to covid), we ate it in the car while listening to music. I also forgot to turn off the heater blower. So of course, we learned her battery was near the end of it's life when the car wouldn't start. No big deal, I had cables in the back. Except the contact points (on her old cables) were rusted and wouldn't work.... Ordered these right away when I got home and they were just what we were looking for. I love the case and the quality is perfect for her small SUV (Subaru Forester).
customer_reviews.author: Blevdog

customer_reviews.title: Clip design is crap, can't grab my bat terminals
customer_reviews.text: An extremely poor design on the clips, only connects well with very exposed battery terminals. It wouldn't work with my Prius.
customer_reviews.author: Kindle Customer

customer_reviews.title: Look/Feel of Good Quality
customer_reviews.text: These look great and appear they will perform when needed. I have not had to use them as I just received them. When and if I do I will update this review. They are contained in a nice zipper case. They look like most other jumper cables and appear/feel of good quality. I bought them because I have a smaller, more compact SUV. When and if the time comes I'll let you know of their performance.
customer_reviews.author: MrDrew

customer_reviews.title: Works great!
customer_reviews.text: I'm a law enforcement officer for a large metro agency. Needless to say, I've run across my fair share of stranded motorists. These cables are long enough to reach if you can't nose to nose the car you're trying to start. The connectors hold strong on the terminal and I've jumped plenty off in just the few weeks I've had it. Can't recommend these more.
customer_reviews.author: Jordan

customer_reviews.title: Great item
customer_reviews.text: Didn't think I needed jumper cables until my battery reminded me. I went food shopping, loaded the car with my items and tried to start my journey home. No dice. I had to call my husband who needed to borrow jumper cables in order to charge my battery. I got home and ordered these heavy duty cables the same day. They were delivered quickly. They now sit in the trunk of my SUV just in case they're needed in the future. My and my car feel better!
customer_reviews.author: Ruth A. Corcoran

customer_reviews.title: Best Value for the $$
customer_reviews.text: Build well, and the cables are not flimsy...will jump start with no problem in a pinch. One can purchase more expensive set, but that all depends if one jumps cars every day? Can't go wrong with this buy! I would stay away from cheaper price points, as the build quality appears to be very low, and the 1st thing to go with the El Cheapo models are the clamps.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Finally  a heavy duty set of cables
customer_reviews.text: After dealing with cheap jumper cables once too often, I bought these. They work! They are heavy gauge and the clamps on the ends will actually grip the battery terminals. I have used these to jump a very high compression LS motor on two occasions with no problem at all. Something that could not be said of my old cheap cables. Not inexpensive, but when you need heavy duty jumper cables, nothing else will do.
customer_reviews.author: Phillip A. Williams

customer_reviews.title: 16' long.
customer_reviews.text: Excellent thickness (2 gauge). Hopefully will be as durable as my last jumper cables (20 years). always buy a longer cable-garages can be tight as well as additional length allowing a car behind the dead one to jump the battery. 12' won't cut it in a lot of situations. 2 Audis side-side, mean there is no room to get out of driver's side car using a 12' cable! The 16' gave comfortable room to jump.
customer_reviews.author: JAcob Kuijper

customer_reviews.title: Solid
customer_reviews.text: For ranch use these have been great - solid, take a high degree of amps/voltage and seem to be holding up nicely. If I were in the towing business I'd probably spend the $200 and get USA made high grade 0 gauge welding wire, but for what I do, these have been just fine. Car and truck jumping only so can't comment outside of that.
customer_reviews.author: Sam Lowry

customer_reviews.title: Tough, Tough, Tough.
customer_reviews.text: Talk about heavy-duty! These are made the way you want jumper cables to be put together. Nothing cheap in the construction or the materials. The canvas bag will hold up bouncing around a trunk. The length will not leave you short. Might be overkill for a Civic, but what you'd want for an F-350!
customer_reviews.author: Tomcat_STL

customer_reviews.title: As described,  excellent product,  well made
customer_reviews.text: Very sturdy, well made product, as described. This will be more than plenty to start my truck or to help somebody stranded. The clamps are really nice and the cable it's really thick, not that flimsy thing i had before that use to get really hot when used. Well done Energizer guys. And the case it's a nice touch
customer_reviews.author: Dino

customer_reviews.title: Solid set for the average person
customer_reviews.text: Needed a basic set of cables as I forgot to remove mine when I sold my Jeep. These are 100% what the average person needs. Price point is excellent as well. Construction is nice, all attachments are sturdy, clamps have great bite, and the case is built well also. I wish there was more solid copper to the clamps and etc, but this is a perfectly fine set for the occasional use.
customer_reviews.author: A2theJackson

customer_reviews.title: Excellent Heavy Duty Jumper Cables
customer_reviews.text: These work great and at 25' long, they allow you to jump a vehicle in front of you or behind you. No more turning around to face the wrong direction. Nice safety feature covers live wires so cables won't spark. Shelled Vinyl coated clamp for rust and corrosion protection. I expect these to last me a lifetime!
customer_reviews.author: Joe Doc

customer_reviews.title: jumper cables
customer_reviews.text: not a big fan of the product name, but these cables appear to be well made and use a good quality gauge cable. I would buy again without hesitation.
customer_reviews.author: JoeAverage-User

customer_reviews.title: Great product
customer_reviews.text: I have needed these for a while and looked at many various offerings. Thus far they are perfect for what I needed. They feel durable, and come with a nice enough canvas style carrying case. I haven't had them in extreme cold yet to rate their flexibility in those situations, but so far they are great for the intended use. Good product!
customer_reviews.author: Mark Britton

customer_reviews.title: Teeth too far back
customer_reviews.text: I bought these to jump Prius from the front, and the teeth on the cables are so far back, i had to force a single tooth against the positive terminal to get a connection
customer_reviews.author: William Peterson

customer_reviews.title: Good Product
customer_reviews.text: If you're like me, you hate tools that don't work. I spent a little more on these cables than you can find others for....but I'm glad I did. They are built well and come with a nice (enough) carry bag. There is no doubt in my mind that when the time comes, these cables will function as they should. They only irk that I have is that they are made in China for a distributor that Energizer hired. These are really just another companies cable with the Energizer name on them....but that's a common marketing practice these days.
customer_reviews.author: C. A. Howe

customer_reviews.title: Big, Thick, Strong, Long cables.  Makes giving a jump easy
customer_reviews.text: I am the jump master. I can reach your car without having to push it to a better position. I don't care what side your battery is on, I can reach it. These big fat wires will flow the power to you. I can jump whatever you got without waiting a day for little wires to move the juice. Seriously, these are beasts and have never failed to get the job done. Jumping big cars with little cables is a pain. If you have the room for them get these. You will be a hero.
customer_reviews.author: James T Stevens III

customer_reviews.title: Glad to have them, hope to not have to use them....
customer_reviews.text: We just took a road trip out West and needed a set of jumper cables to be prepared. Checked all the reviews on several products but Energizer stood out. More power, longer cables, more extra benefits, better reviews, so it was a no-brainer! We choose Energizer, even tho we did not need them on our trip, it was great not to have to worry because we knew we were covered. Very satisfied with our purchase.
customer_reviews.author: lisa coker

customer_reviews.title: WOW, great quality, heavy duty item!
customer_reviews.text: Truly a great quality Heavy Duty jumper cable and this item is heavy in weight too. Great for truck charging to trailer/Fifth Wheel batteries because of length and HD gauge of wire. This wire is copper coated aluminum multi-strand (striated wire) for increased amperage flow. I feel pure solid copper striated wire would be much heavier and definitely cost a lot more. I am very happy for the quality and price, thus I would highly recommend this item.
customer_reviews.author: Slim

customer_reviews.title: Best jumper cables purchase I have ever made
customer_reviews.text: I purchased these after watching a top 10 on EZvid.wiki. I am very impressed with these jumper cables. I own 2 diesel truck which has trained me to be cautious and over buy when I can. The value price of these cables allows me to safely start my trucks without fear of fire. There also is a heavy duty case included that appears to be durable enough to last being used more than once.
customer_reviews.author: Jean-Paul V

customer_reviews.title: There are better cables out there
customer_reviews.text: The cables themselves seem sturdy enough. But the clamps on the ends are very oddly shaped. I have tried them on several different old and newer batteries and they just have such a weird shape to them they don’t really get a good grip on anything. They slip off very easily.
customer_reviews.author: Camp Guy

customer_reviews.title: Great Heavy duty jumper cables.
customer_reviews.text: I have used many different types and gauges of cables and this is one of the best. Heavy duty, well made and long enough for most any jump start you may need. We will really see about the true sturdiness and durability after I have owned them for good length of time. Highly recommended!
customer_reviews.author: Xavierklaw

customer_reviews.title: Unquestionably heavy duty!
customer_reviews.text: Needed to replace jumper cables in my Explorer. These appear to be VERY sturdy and certainly long enough to jump from the weirdest of parked angles. Nice that they come in a compact, seemingly heavy duty, fabric case. I can't imagine ever needing another set!
customer_reviews.author: Chelle

customer_reviews.title: Quality of product, price and Customer Service is OUTSTANDING!!!
customer_reviews.text: I liked that the quality for the cables was not light weight and cheap compared to many off brands I have seen in many stores. I also loved the storage bag that they come shipped in can be great to use for storing the cables easily and compactly in my tire wheel well. Company was quick on delivery and communicates and appreciates customers.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Great Value! Buy it!
customer_reviews.text: Just what I was LQQking for! It's much heavier than I expected. For the occasional use of my needs, I should have bought the 4 gauge set. Oh well...I'm happy! I just may gift this one and buy the lighter duty set. Not for the money savings, but for the reason I just don't need this industrial-strength set. Great value! Buy it!
customer_reviews.author: BigBadDad

customer_reviews.title: Good pair of cables - 16 feet of cable is practical
customer_reviews.text: I like these cables, and I like the 16 feet of cable. You will realize this if you have ever tried to jump a battery and your cables run a little short, and you have to keep repositioning the cars. With 16 feet of cable, that problem is pretty much solved. (Putting the cables back in that nice compact back is a wee bit of a chore, but they do fit!) I am very happy with this purchase. I'd recommend these cables. They do not take up a lot of space in a vehicle, and they are a must-have.
customer_reviews.author: CaliGal

customer_reviews.title: Great product for use on a top post battery!
customer_reviews.text: The reviews and descriptions state they work great with top post or side post batteries. They do work great with top post batteries. They fail miserably with side post batteries. They don't line up well and they don't have enough teeth at the edges to hook on the side of the battery terminals. The cables are thick and sturdy but if you have a side post battery you may be disappointed like I am.
customer_reviews.author: Nola Redd

customer_reviews.title: Good Quality
customer_reviews.text: Have not jumped a car with them yet, but they are of good quality. The ones I got had jaws just like the picture, bunny branded and everything. Seem like they will work great. Bag is a little cheap, but it's a bag. Probably end up unraveling them after the first use anyway.
customer_reviews.author: Regmanabq

customer_reviews.title: The bag is not adding value to the product.
customer_reviews.text: If you feel that the bag is worth something, it will require a very tight and precise winding the cables to fit them back into the bag. Not something that you would like to pay attention to when you have to put it back after starting a car with dead battery. If Energizer wants to include a "gift" they could have made it bigger.
customer_reviews.author: adygil

customer_reviews.title: it was amazing. These are thick cables that simply will not ...
customer_reviews.text: I cannot rave enough about what high quality this set of cables is. I had to jump a car parked behind me a few weeks ago... it was amazing. These are thick cables that simply will not get tangled. 5 stars to the Energizer!
customer_reviews.author: Dave in Nashville TN

customer_reviews.title: Excellent wherever you're parked
customer_reviews.text: Needed a set for teenager's car. This was perfect. Zippered case to keep them neatly stored, and extra length so you can jump from behind or side as well as front. Great idea, since often you're pulled into a space when battery dies! Would recommend for any driver.
customer_reviews.author: Michael Maggard

customer_reviews.title: Nice jumpers
customer_reviews.text: They have a special side mount jaw to use on battery cables that are connected to the side. Good gauge for stronger jump capacity. I would buy again. Come with a case and info on correct procedure to use the cables.
customer_reviews.author: Jay

customer_reviews.title: Handy. A must have!
customer_reviews.text: My wife’s car could not be turned on because she did not drive it for a long time because of covid. The battery needed a boost and this product definitely helped with it. Be mindful of the Gauge value. This one is perfect
customer_reviews.author: Colonel

customer_reviews.title: Very happy with these jumper cables after owning them for a ...
customer_reviews.text: Very happy with these jumper cables after owning them for a while, now. Easily jumped a couple passenger diesels, which smaller cables can have trouble with. Would be nice if the case that they came in was a) slightly higher quality and b) actually big enough to fit the cables back in without being a magician.
customer_reviews.author: Conor

customer_reviews.title: Great cables! Opt for the 20ft cables
customer_reviews.text: Awesome cables! Very good quality. I bought the 2 gauge, 16ft cables. I wish I would have gone with the 20ft. Shortly after buying them I had to use them and couldn’t reach the other car (from the back). So definitely recommend going with the longer set!
customer_reviews.author: Carlos Aguilo

customer_reviews.title: Great for the price, manageable length, w/ bag
customer_reviews.text: Flexible, soft wire, strong clamps, not bad for the price point. I got the 16ft option as I thought all of the 1 or 2 gauge options that were 20 plus feet long would be bulkier heavier and clumsier than needed. I would have even liked 12 ft set but they only come in lighter gauge wire.
customer_reviews.author: OK Corral

customer_reviews.title: As Described
customer_reviews.text: So, my 40 year old cables were basically useless when my battery died. I bought a new battery and installed but would have rather jumped and drove to town. PLEASE know that I have not used yet BUT, I unpacked and tok a close look and I am satisfied that these will do the job when needed. Better cable, better clamps, longer length and better rating.
customer_reviews.author: wacoed

customer_reviews.title: Bought these because they are a great name and needed longer cables to reach from front ...
customer_reviews.text: Bought these because they are a great name and needed longer cables to reach from front to back. Had a situation, so I upgraded to longer ones. It took me 5 times to wind the cables back in the storage bag. There is no extra room in the bag. Called Energizer 1-877-744-7220 to give them feedback, a little wiggle room in the storage bag is needed. For such high quality cables why not!?
customer_reviews.author: Nia w.

customer_reviews.title: Sturdy
customer_reviews.text: I really can’t give us an adequate rating. Because the car I was jumpstarting would not start. I don’t think it’s the fault of the jumper cables, I think the battery is either beyond jumping or there’s another problem.
customer_reviews.author: jaskjk

customer_reviews.title: Best product I have bought
customer_reviews.text: in the winter my car wasn.t on for a week. I got sick and had to run to a doctor and my car did not start. I called the mechanic asked to pay 40$ for a jump start. luckily my neighbor had this in his car. he helped me out. and I decided to but this. a most important part of the car.
customer_reviews.author: avinash garud

customer_reviews.title: Seems good... Have not jumped anything yet
customer_reviews.text: Came packaged well. The material case is nice, but I doubt once I take them out and unfold them I will ever get them back into that case. I checked continuity and it was OK. Until I use them to jump start, won't know conclusively how it works.
customer_reviews.author: gogo

customer_reviews.title: Energizer jumper cables met a need
customer_reviews.text: This set of jumper cables from Energizer appear to be well made and I felt they were a reasonable value. Most of the time we buy something like this as a precaution and usually only need them a few times over the years. We expect reliability. I'm satisfied with my decision.
customer_reviews.author: Codger

customer_reviews.title: Perform as advertised
customer_reviews.text: No one seems to carry jumper cables anymore and I seem to have someone ask for help every couple of months. These cables are heavyweight and the length gives me no problem in doing jumps. While I still like the ones my dad made for me over 40 years ago, these are longer and my are my go to cables. Recommend to all.
customer_reviews.author: Kram

customer_reviews.title: Better to have them and not need them than to having to need them and not having them!
customer_reviews.text: The 25 feet is exactly what I needed to jump the batteries in the equipment I run. Enough length for me to pull my suburban up to the machine and more! Even though they're CCA,I really don't need much. Disconnect the 2 batteries and charge them for 15-20 minutes each (12 volt jumping 24 volt) . As for jump starting cars? Its perfect! You can pull up to behind OR in front of the disabled vehicle ! 25 feet is definitely enough!
customer_reviews.author: Johnny dammit

customer_reviews.title: Energizer is awesome!
customer_reviews.text: This was our second set but not because they broke we just wanted a second set! Nice heavy duty cable and clamp. Love them, my coworkers all know to come to me for my cables. Very excited that the same quality cables in a nicer pouch than the old ones.
customer_reviews.author: D. McCarthy

customer_reviews.title: Can’t wait to use
customer_reviews.text: Broke down yesterday and couldn’t find anyone who had jumper cables so I deceived to go on amazon and get my own and after I read the good reviews on this I decided to purchase these. I can’t wait to use them weather on me or to help someone else.
customer_reviews.author: Adrienne

customer_reviews.title: Great Quality!
customer_reviews.text: While I haven’t needed to use these cables, the quality seems to be very solid. My husband is the so-called mechanic, lol, and he thinks they’re good quality. We’ll wait & see but so far, am very happy with how quickly they arrived (4 days) and the carrying case is an added plus. Happy with my purchase.
customer_reviews.author: Mie Stricoff

customer_reviews.title: Very thick and high quality
customer_reviews.text: I bought these to replace an old pair that had dry rotted. These are VERY thick and seem solid. The length options are great too. I have an Audi with a battery in the trunk. Many other cars have them up front, and this helps allow for more options in not having to maneuver around a car that is dead in its tracks.
customer_reviews.author: lee silverman

customer_reviews.title: Great cables.  Will never go back into the carrying case
customer_reviews.text: There isn't a hope in the that the cables will ever fit back into the tiny back they were packed in. but the cables work great. luckily I have a large storage area under the back seat in my truck.
customer_reviews.author: Captain Obvious

customer_reviews.title: Great quality cables
customer_reviews.text: These cables are great even in the cold Minnesota winters! The cables stay flexible and they are plenty long so you don't need to worry about jockeying cars around. The clamps are a bit oversized which makes them difficult to use in a tight engine compartment, but that's my only complaint.
customer_reviews.author: R. Brodowicz

customer_reviews.title: Very Sturdy
customer_reviews.text: I cannot give this a review as of yet, because I have not used them yet. I will say I like the way they came packaged in their case and the time I received them. I just gave it 4 stars due to the fact I have not used them yet (hoping I do not have to, but they do look like a good pair of cables.
customer_reviews.author: Ms.Mack

customer_reviews.title: Excellent and professional
customer_reviews.text: Very professional: beautiful 2ga wires with thick covering. The clamps are sturdy and have a strong spring. The 20 ft length enables connecting a car behind my van. The carrying case is very sturdy - not plastic.
customer_reviews.author: Michael G. Sklar

customer_reviews.title: Quality Cables
customer_reviews.text: I looked around for a good set of cables to put in my Jeep and am very happy with these. They come in a nice smaller tote bag to store away behind my seats. I was surprised at how small the bag was considering the thickness of the cables
customer_reviews.author: bittersweet

customer_reviews.title: Reliability
customer_reviews.text: The product arrived in good condition. It comes with a handy case rather than having a loose cable in your vehicle. The clamp design is unique with the ability to connect to various battery terminal sizes and configurations. I would have preferred 100% copper wire, but that would significantly increase the product's cost. The current rating is more than adequate for the vast majority of battery boost requirements.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: good cables
customer_reviews.text: this is a pretty decent set of cables for the price, not the most heavy duty, got them for my DAD, worried about him not having a set in his truck case works good, slide them right under seat for easy access, out of the way, he is Happy ,

customer_reviews.title: Pay attention when unpacking
customer_reviews.text: Just go the cables. So far so good. The only complaint is on the first three tries it’s annoyingly difficult to fit them back in the bag. Pay close attention to how the ya re wrapped up when you first remove them.
customer_reviews.author: JS

customer_reviews.title: Works as advertised
customer_reviews.text: I purchased ENB-216 to provide supplement power to my vehicle while reflashing the ECU via a Cobb Accessport. This was more than sufficient for the process as the Cobb AP complained there was too much voltage to allow the process to continue. The length and durability of this product will be perfect should we ever find ourselves stranded with a dead battery.
customer_reviews.author: John Persons

customer_reviews.title: Energizer Jumper Cables
customer_reviews.text: They seem to be very sturdy cables. The handles are a little smaller than I'm used to but the spring seems strong enough and they open enough for clamping on top posts. Time will tell there longevity. There's nothing to complain about so far. I would recommend these cables.
customer_reviews.author: Bob

customer_reviews.title: Greatest jumpers I’ve owned
customer_reviews.text: Very durable. The clamps are tough. The clamps are so tough that it removed my battery connector when I attempted to unclamped from the battery. Just used it to jump my F350. Super happy with purchase.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: wow! very impressed
customer_reviews.text: great bang for the buck but also extreme Heavy Duty cables -industrial is fair to say but packs away nice. Bag is one and done won't fit back in the bag regardless Ill be buying a second pair for my other truck here soon
customer_reviews.author: Andrew F.

customer_reviews.title: Quality
customer_reviews.text: Needed a new set of jumpers for my new car (hopefully never have to use them). For the price I figured I would give them a try, glad I did. Right away you can tell these are quality jumpers.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Sturdy and Flexible!
customer_reviews.text: These jumper cables by energizer are sturdy made while also being extremely flexible (even at low temperatures). I hope that neither of us would ever need to use them but it is important to have them in the trunk for emergencies.
customer_reviews.author: Elias

customer_reviews.title: Great cables. If you have a big V8 or ...
customer_reviews.text: Great cables. If you have a big V8 or a diesel, these are the only way to go. No waiting a half hour for the battery to charge up using cables that are too small to carry the load. I own a large independent auto repair business and these are the best cables I've seen at ANY price. They cost a few bucks, but the battery never goes dead at a convenient time. These cables allow you to access another vehicle's battery no matter how you are parked. 25 feet will reach it! And the 1-gauge wire will handle the load.
customer_reviews.author: Tim

customer_reviews.title: Cables
customer_reviews.text: This product arrived in a nice package and was on time. The cables are sturdy and I will have these for a long time. My only issue is the average citizen will not use these cables on a regular basis and I would like the warranty on this product to extend to at least 5 years.
customer_reviews.author: Cedric Davis

customer_reviews.title: Great price and arrived ahead of schedule.
customer_reviews.text: I haven't had occasion to use the cables yet, and hope I never need to because I don't like it when the battery dies. That said, the price was great and it arrived on Tuesday, even though it could have arrived by Friday and still been within the on time window. I trust they will serve us well when necessary and last a long time. I therefore am happy to recommend them to others.
customer_reviews.author: George L. Fuller

customer_reviews.title: A heavy duty jumper cable for all amp requirements
customer_reviews.text: The cables are heavy duty with a strong and heavy duty clamp. I purposely chose the higher amp cables to be able to pull all the needed amps when having to jump off any vehicle. The carry case is an added bonus that makes storage in my trunk a breeze
customer_reviews.author: Pete

customer_reviews.title: Great value , seems of excellent quality
customer_reviews.text: Needed a set to throw in spare older vehicle, these were perfect. Heavy duty quality, case is a nice touch. Great value here. Super fast shipping . No issues, very happy
customer_reviews.author: Chris

customer_reviews.title: quality jumper cables
customer_reviews.text: We'd meant to just buy alligator clips for our old set of cables but then my husband found this pair for LESS yet a higher quality of cable and longer than we had. He's very pleased with the cables now that he's received them.
customer_reviews.author: teche

customer_reviews.title: Heavy Duty Gear!
customer_reviews.text: One thing you can bet on: These cables will never fray and the clamps will be in great working order long after we've all become fodder for archeologists! Seriously, super heavy duty, sturdy gear.
customer_reviews.author: crazyredj

customer_reviews.title: THE BEST...
customer_reviews.text: They were just what I was looking for, battery got drained and all I had was one of those lighter jumpers..LOL..went home and ordered these and am happy as heck...
customer_reviews.author: Louis Heller
